                    },
                    "body": "Also keep in mind that in addition to binding to different Auth Adapters, it can be bound to different Storage Mechanisms.. With that in mind, if component A and component B really want to maintain different authentication identities (extreme edge case), they can both do so within the same session, simply by using a different namespace in the ZendSession storage type adapter.\n\ngetInstance (like Zend_Contoller) should be complemented with a resetInstance().",
